<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,215,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,215,241]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(modified after 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[470,605,216,242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 860" refId="ref55290" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, I - VII, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">Cook 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[620,788,216,242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="97 - 105" refId="ref55521" refString="Gerecke, R. (1992) A remarkable new Nilotonia - species from the Pollino Mountains (Southern Italy) (Acari, Actinedida, Nilotoniidae). Spixiana, 15, 97 - 105." type="journal article" year="1992">Gerecke 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Goldschmidt, T." box="[803,1041,216,242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="113 - 150" refId="ref55708" refString="Goldschmidt, T. (2004 b) Untersuchungen uber Wassermilben der Familie Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910 aus der Neotropis (Acari, Actinedida, Hydrachnidia). Senckenbergiana biologica, 83 (2), 113 - 150." type="journal article" year="2004">Goldschmidt 2004b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Panesar, A. R." box="[1055,1216,216,242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref56187" refString="Panesar, A. R. (2004) Evolution in water mites (Hydrachnellae, Actinedida, Acari). A revision of the Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910. Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 52, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2004">Panesar 2004</bibRefCitation>
): Dorsum bearing two small post-ocular platelets and one larger postero-medial plate (from relatively small platelets to large plates, sometimes even fused); secondary sclerotization of venter absent to extensive, especially at caudal margin of Cx-IV and post-genital sclerite (in some species secondary sclerotization of Cx-IV fused with postgenital sclerite, forming ventral shield); coxae in four groups, Cx-I and Cx-II medially separated or fused, suture between Cx-III and Cx-IV variable; leg-IV-6 without claws, with terminal peg-like setae and none, one or several larger sub-terminal setae; well developed terminal claws on leg-I to leg-III without, with single or with several clawlets; palp typical for the family.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,215,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,535,561]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks:</emphasis>
The diagnosis of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1905" box="[675,786,536,561]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[675,786,536,561]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still remains very broad, including a wide variety of characters and the number and separation of subgenera is unclear. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad, O." box="[926,1123,576,602]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="391 - 525" refId="ref55955" refString="Lundblad, O. (1952) Hydracarinen von den ostafrikanischen Gebirgen. Arkiv for Zoologi, Serie 2, 3 (31), 391 - 525." type="journal article" year="1952">Lundblad (1952)</bibRefCitation>
separated the African species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1905" box="[235,346,616,641]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[235,346,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the completeness or incompleteness of the suture between Cx-III and Cx-IV in the subgenera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1952" box="[279,398,656,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Neodartia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[279,398,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Neodartia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1929" box="[458,565,656,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dartiella">
<emphasis box="[458,565,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Dartiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; meanwhile both have been synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1905" box="[1136,1247,656,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1136,1247,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1256,1319,656,682]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref56494" refString="Viets, K. (1956) Die Milben des Susswassers und des Meeres. Hydrachnellae et Halacaridae (Acari). II. und III. Teil: Katalog und Nomenklator. Fischer Verlag, Jena, 870 pp." type="book" year="1956">Viets 1956</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[224,358,696,722]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 860" refId="ref55290" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, I - VII, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">Cook 1974</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[377,525,696,722]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 860" refId="ref55290" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, I - VII, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">Cook (1974)</bibRefCitation>
as well as K.O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K. O." box="[716,860,696,722]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref56590" refString="Viets, K. O. (1987) Die Milben des Susswassers (Hydrachnellae und Halacaridae [part.], Acari). 2: Katalog. Sonderbande des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, 8, 1012 pp." type="book" year="1987">Viets (1987)</bibRefCitation>
separate five subgenera within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1905" box="[1230,1341,696,721]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1230,1341,696,721]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly by means of the number of terminal/sub-terminal setae on leg-IV-6, sexual dimorphism on leg-II-5, presence/ absence of swimming hairs and degree of secondary sclerotization. Following K.O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K. O." box="[1147,1296,776,802]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref56590" refString="Viets, K. O. (1987) Die Milben des Susswassers (Hydrachnellae und Halacaridae [part.], Acari). 2: Katalog. Sonderbande des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, 8, 1012 pp." type="book" year="1987">Viets (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, all African species (except of one species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soar" authorityYear="1917" box="[706,784,816,841]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Dartia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,784,816,841]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Dartia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) belong to the principle subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1905" box="[1194,1305,816,841]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1194,1305,816,841]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1313,1371,816,842]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" sensu="stricto">s. str</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. In a redefinition and re-organisation of the subgenera of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Panesar (2004)" authorityName=", Panesar" authorityYear="2004" box="[769,1072,856,882]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[769,880,856,881]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Panesar, A. R." box="[895,1072,856,882]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref56187" refString="Panesar, A. R. (2004) Evolution in water mites (Hydrachnellae, Actinedida, Acari). A revision of the Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910. Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 52, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2004">Panesar (2004)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
separated seven (partly different) subgenera also including size and arrangement of the acetabula as well as length relations of the medial coxal suture of Cx-I and the genital field into taxonomic diagnosis. He shifted most African species to the subgenera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1929" box="[236,343,976,1001]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dartiella">
<emphasis box="[236,343,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Dartiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[401,530,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Manotonia</emphasis>
. As the 
<typeStatus box="[628,678,976,1002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus — 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nordenskiold, 1905)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Nordenskiold" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[965,1435,976,1002]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricata">
<emphasis box="[965,1176,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia loricata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nordenskiold, N. E." box="[1191,1428,976,1002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref56009" refString="Nordenskiold, N. E. (1905) Hydrachniden aus dem Sudan. In: Jagerskiold, A. (Ed), Results of the Swedish zoological Expedition to Egypt and the White Nile. Vol. 2. Library of the Royal University, Uppsala, pp. 1 - 12." type="book" year="1905">Nordenskiöld, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
— possess true swimming hairs, only two species from Africa and two from 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1111,1016,1042]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">India</collectingCountry>
are included in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Panesar" authorityYear="2004" box="[1299,1410,1016,1041]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Nilotonia</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="7" pageNumber="8" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Panesar, A. R." box="[204,370,1056,1082]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref56187" refString="Panesar, A. R. (2004) Evolution in water mites (Hydrachnellae, Actinedida, Acari). A revision of the Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910. Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 52, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2004">Panesar 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Until additional information (larval descriptions, morphology of genital skeleton, morphology of all legs in all species, molecular data) on most species are available, I am following the present subgeneric classification by 
<bibRefCitation author="Panesar, A. R." box="[494,678,1136,1162]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref56187" refString="Panesar, A. R. (2004) Evolution in water mites (Hydrachnellae, Actinedida, Acari). A revision of the Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910. Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 52, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2004">Panesar (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. However, as the separation of the subgenera is still relatively weak, often based upon very few characteristics and with many exceptions, in the following remarks to the new species the differences to similar species in other subgenera (and sometimes even similar genera) are also discussed. With regard to the new material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Panesar" authorityYear="2004" box="[692,803,1256,1281]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[692,803,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(especially the subgenera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[1116,1255,1256,1281]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Telotaolana">
<emphasis box="[1116,1255,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Telotaolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Goldschmidt, 2008" authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2008" box="[1312,1426,1256,1281]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Cookonia">
<emphasis box="[1312,1426,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cookonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from 
<collectingCountry box="[221,364,1296,1322]" name="Madagascar" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<emphasis box="[382,530,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mamersonia</emphasis>
(K. Viets, 1954) — classified as an independent genus by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goldschmidt, T." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="113 - 150" refId="ref55708" refString="Goldschmidt, T. (2004 b) Untersuchungen uber Wassermilben der Familie Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910 aus der Neotropis (Acari, Actinedida, Hydrachnidia). Senckenbergiana biologica, 83 (2), 113 - 150." type="journal article" year="2004">Goldschmidt (2004b)</bibRefCitation>
, regarded as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Panesar" authorityYear="2004" box="[573,684,1336,1361]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[573,684,1336,1361]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Panesar, A. R." box="[730,907,1336,1362]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref56187" refString="Panesar, A. R. (2004) Evolution in water mites (Hydrachnellae, Actinedida, Acari). A revision of the Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910. Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 52, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2004">Panesar (2004)</bibRefCitation>
— again has to be considered as a subgenus within 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Panesar" authorityYear="2004" box="[233,344,1376,1401]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[233,344,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nilotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
